1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,000
<i>Get out of that station
right now.</i>

2
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:13,500
<i>Didn't I tell you,
you can't leave?</i>

3
00:00:13,633 --> 00:00:14,767
<i>Chief, we have
a family emergency.</i>

4
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:15,733
<i> I need to go home.</i>

5
00:00:15,867 --> 00:00:17,233
<i> Don't you dare leave!</i>

6
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:20,967
<i> What are you doing?</i>

7
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> I said get out!</i>

8
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:25,267
<i> Robles is something else.</i>

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:26,500
<i>He's very good
at covering his tracks.</i>

10
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:27,867
<i> I'm sorry,</i>

11
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,100
<i> but let's see who'll go first.</i>

12
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:30,800
<i>Oh my! There's a cop
who went amok!</i>

13
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:32,167
<i>He's now holding
his colleagues hostage</i>

14
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:33,967
<i>- at Station 12.
- What?</i>

15
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,133
<i> Surrender now.</i>

16
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:37,467
<i>I'm going to make you
a state witness.</i>

17
00:00:37,600 --> 00:00:38,733
<i> That can only mean one thing.</i>

18
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:40,267
<i>He already found out
that we already know...</i>

19
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,367
<i> he's part of the syndicate.</i>

20
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,700
<i> What does Robles need?</i>

21
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,400
<i>Helicopter.
He gave a deadline.</i>

22
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:45,967
<i>Thirty minutes if
the helicopter is not here,</i>

23
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:47,533
<i>He will kill
one of his hostages.</i>

24
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:49,433
<i>Sir, the major is getting weak.</i>

25
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,233
<i>Let us take him to the hospital.</i>

26
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,367
<i> Sir, what's with you?</i>

27
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:53,633
<i>You're making so much noise
for a while now!</i>

28
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:55,833
<i> Robles, what's with you?</i>

29
00:00:55,967 --> 00:00:57,933
<i>The Mayor's order
is to surrender,</i>

30
00:00:58,067 --> 00:00:59,400
<i> but not to the police.</i>

31
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:01,300
<i> You'll surrender to him.</i>

32
00:01:01,433 --> 00:01:02,567
<i>I'll wait for the boss to call.</i>

33
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:05,433
<i>Just tell him that nothing bad
will happen to me.</i>

34
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:07,333
<i>The time I've been waiting
for is over.</i>

35
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,467
<i> That means I can kill now.</i>

36
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:10,500
<i> That's it.</i>

37
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:13,967
<i> Eenie meenie miney mo.</i>

38
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:18,900
Hey, Bobby!

39
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:21,000
What are you doing?

40
00:01:21,133 --> 00:01:22,033
Isn't it obvious?

41
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:23,800
She's going to go to work.

42
00:01:23,933 --> 00:01:25,367
But, Bobby, why?

43
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:27,833
Oh, my friends are being
hostaged.

44
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:29,467
I need to help them.

45
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,500
Wait...

46
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:31,800
It seems like just now...

47
00:01:31,933 --> 00:01:34,300
you were thinking about
resigning from your police job.

48
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,867
And now, you're in a hurry.

49
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,167
Mar, this is an emergency
situation.

50
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:39,967
So what if your resignation
is finalized...

51
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,867
and another emergency happens?

52
00:01:42,033 --> 00:01:43,867
Will you rush to help again?

53
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Bobby, we're just reminding you,
okay?

54
00:01:46,133 --> 00:01:47,333
Didn't your godmother...

55
00:01:47,467 --> 00:01:51,100
respond to the emergency even
though she was on leave?

56
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:54,267
Bobby, do you remember what
happened to your godmother?

57
00:02:04,033 --> 00:02:05,567
<i> Godmother!</i>

58
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:11,933
<i> Godmother, Godmother!</i>

59
00:02:12,067 --> 00:02:13,567
<i> Godmother!</i>

60
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:16,167
<i> Godmother! Godmother!</i>

61
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:18,067
<i> Godmother!</i>

62
00:02:20,867 --> 00:02:22,067
Oh, right?

63
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,100
Your Godmother Dina never
returned to her family!

64
00:02:25,233 --> 00:02:26,500
So what if now,

65
00:02:26,633 --> 00:02:29,267
you can't return to your
Grandmother Isang?

66
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:31,467
So, who will you choose, Bobby?

67
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:35,200
The captain or your police job?

68
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:38,633
You know the answer
to the question.

69
00:02:38,767 --> 00:02:40,133
- Bobby!
- Bobby, hey, hey.

70
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:42,067
- Hey!
- Hey!

71
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,200
Hey, what the heck?

72
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:45,967
You're making a lot of noise
in the morning.

73
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,833
Oh my!

74
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,400
Oh, my grandchild!

75
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:53,867
You came home from work early.

76
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:58,133
I missed you, Bobby,
I missed you.

77
00:03:55,967 --> 00:03:58,300
Robles...

78
00:03:58,433 --> 00:04:01,267
Release Bautista and chief.

79
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,400
Those guys have families.

80
00:04:03,533 --> 00:04:06,433
Just hold me hostage.

81
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:10,500
Did I tell you
to open your mouth?

82
00:04:10,633 --> 00:04:12,233
Don't blame me,

83
00:04:12,367 --> 00:04:13,667
the people outside.

84
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,033
I've been waiting for my request
for a while now.

85
00:04:16,167 --> 00:04:17,967
Until now, nothing!

86
00:04:29,167 --> 00:04:30,767
Bok!

87
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,500
Bok, this is Tonyo!

88
00:04:32,633 --> 00:04:34,167
Let's talk!

89
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,867
How's chief?

90
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,733
Bok...

91
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:42,567
We're doing okay here.

92
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:45,067
Chief, he's still alive.

93
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,167
But I just don't know how long.

94
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,367
This Bautista, she's wounded,
but only a little.

95
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,633
Maybe later,
I'll follow Dizon next.

96
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:01,967
Bok, what's the news?

97
00:05:02,133 --> 00:05:05,467
Did you and Garcia get anything
from my house?

98
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,500
Oh...

99
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:11,933
Robles, best friend!

100
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:15,633
Oh, how are you doing there?

101
00:05:15,767 --> 00:05:16,767
Why are you acting that way.

102
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,367
What happened to you?

103
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:21,433
Garcia, are you there too?

104
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:24,633
Do you want to come in here,
change places with Dizon?

105
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:26,033
That can be arranged.

106
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:28,300
Oh, no, I'm okay here.

107
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:31,000
You're closer to Dizon.

108
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,100
Bok...

109
00:05:36,233 --> 00:05:39,133
it's not too late.

110
00:05:39,267 --> 00:05:42,100
Let us help you!

111
00:05:42,233 --> 00:05:44,467
Just surrender,

112
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:50,133
I promise I'll do anything
to reduce your sentence.

113
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:52,433
I'm reminding you.

114
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:55,733
It's not you we want to arrest,

115
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:59,733
but whoever the head of the
syndicate is.

116
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:03,267
Noble, where's the SWAT?

117
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:04,867
Ma'am, there's no update yet.

118
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:08,833
Lieutenant, the mayor is here.

119
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:12,533
Mayor.

120
00:06:12,667 --> 00:06:14,233
Let me talk to
the hostage taker.

121
00:06:14,367 --> 00:06:16,533
I'll try to plead.

122
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:17,633
That's not possible.

123
00:06:17,767 --> 00:06:19,533
There's an ongoing negotiation.

124
00:06:19,667 --> 00:06:21,033
Please, Lieutenant Samson.

125
00:06:21,167 --> 00:06:24,000
Maybe I can help before someone
else loses their life.

126
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:26,267
Mayor, it's really not possible.

127
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,167
What you want to happen
is more dangerous.

128
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,833
Let's just wait for the update.

129
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:35,933
You know, Conde,

130
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:38,567
I really admire you.

131
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:41,133
Of all the police officers,
you are the most honest.

132
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:45,367
You don't have a single blemish
on your body.

133
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:47,067
You know, of all the police
officers I've met,

134
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:50,167
you are my idol.

135
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:52,400
That's what I dreamed of
when I was just starting out

136
00:06:52,533 --> 00:06:55,200
to be a good police officer.

137
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:56,633
But I realized
there's nothing to gain...

138
00:06:56,767 --> 00:06:58,567
if I become
a good police officer.

139
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:01,267
It's just that it's hard
to get promoted.

140
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:02,767
It's hard to get rich.

141
00:07:02,900 --> 00:07:04,800
It's hard to make money.

142
00:07:04,933 --> 00:07:06,967
Maybe, later, I'll retire...

143
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:10,033
and grow old without having
gained anything from this.

144
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:12,367
Oh...

145
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:14,233
Robles!

146
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,200
Your problem is only money!

147
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:18,033
I can help you!

148
00:07:18,167 --> 00:07:20,567
My credit card has
a high credit limit.

149
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:22,000
I know someone at the bank.

150
00:07:22,133 --> 00:07:24,133
I'll refer you.

151
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:27,667
You know, you really are crazy,
Garcia!

152
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,767
Of all the police officers
I've met,

153
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:33,367
you, you're the most worthless!

154
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:34,767
You're all talk.

155
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:37,133
You have so many excuses.

156
00:07:37,267 --> 00:07:38,800
With a woman,
there's nothing you can do.

157
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:40,167
You're always getting let down,
right?

158
00:07:40,300 --> 00:07:43,233
You're always let down!

159
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:45,667
Besides, aren't you ashamed

160
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:50,033
that all the cases you've solved
are because of Tonyo?

161
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,267
Can you hear me?

162
00:07:57,667 --> 00:08:00,000
Bok...

163
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:02,333
we'll help you...

164
00:08:02,467 --> 00:08:04,700
just show me...

165
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,500
who your boss is
in the syndicate.

166
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:09,833
Bok, forgive me,

167
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:12,833
but I can't do that now.

168
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:13,733
I need to finish everything

169
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:17,300
I started until the end.

170
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:21,100
Wait...

171
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:24,967
where's the helicopter
I asked for?

172
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:29,567
Thirty minutes have passed,
still nothing!

173
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,433
That means I can kill
someone here.

174
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:32,667
No, no, no! Bok!

175
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:34,833
Bok, the helicopter
is on its way.

176
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:36,167
Oh, five minutes!

177
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:39,133
I'm not stupid, Garcia!

178
00:08:39,267 --> 00:08:42,467
I know that too because
I've studied that too!

179
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,533
<i>Conde, the helicopter
is on its way.</i>

180
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:45,833
<i> Let Robles go.</i>

181
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:46,900
<i>Our priority is
to get them back.</i>

182
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:48,967
There! There!

183
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,333
This is the truth!

184
00:08:50,467 --> 00:08:52,867
From Samson, my loves.

185
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,233
What are you waiting for, Conde?

186
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,767
Get out of there,

187
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:59,067
and when I escape, save Chief.

188
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:04,867
Okay, Bok, we'll go out,

189
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,533
but promise.

190
00:09:07,667 --> 00:09:11,100
Don't hurt our companions
inside.

191
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:13,733
Okay, Bok, that's a promise.

192
00:09:13,867 --> 00:09:15,967
Okay, hurry up!

193
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:21,900
Robles...

194
00:09:22,033 --> 00:09:23,500
Robles, surrender.

195
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,933
There's still hope.

196
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:29,833
I'll help you.

197
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,700
Chief, you know...

198
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:49,300
I know you treated me
like your own son.

199
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,067
I'm sorry.

200
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,233
I just got a little lost.

201
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:00,233
I just want to say,

202
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:02,400
thank you very, very, very much

203
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:04,600
for all the help
you've given me.

204
00:10:17,733 --> 00:10:20,433
Dizon...

205
00:10:20,567 --> 00:10:23,000
you take care of chief, okay?

206
00:10:23,133 --> 00:10:25,533
If anything bad happens to him,

207
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:27,867
I'll kill you.

208
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,733
Do you understand?

209
00:10:37,633 --> 00:10:39,200
- Stand up!
- Hey, Robles!

210
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:40,600
Where are you taking Bautista?

211
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:42,467
Stand up!

212
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,533
Sir!

213
00:10:43,667 --> 00:10:45,033
Hey, Robles!

214
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:48,933
<i> It's been a few minutes...</i>

215
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:53,133
<i>since the police and the hostage
taker had a negotiation.</i>

216
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:55,533
<i>We don't know
what's going on inside...</i>

217
00:10:55,667 --> 00:10:57,967
<i>and if the hostages
are safe or not.</i>

218
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,267
<i> Don't let go for more updates.</i>

219
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,067
Who were the police officers
who went in?

220
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,000
Was it Tonyo?

221
00:11:03,133 --> 00:11:04,633
The reporter didn't say
anything.

222
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:07,067
But, Bobby, who do you think?

223
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,400
Because I don't see...

224
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:10,367
Tonyo and Sir Eric outside.

225
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:13,700
Oh my, so they went in?

226
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:16,133
Oh no, I hope they're safe!

227
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:24,933
Sir...

228
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:28,633
Sir...

229
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:08,700
Bok...

230
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:10,967
go ahead, Bok, do it.

231
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:13,100
It seems like I'm already dead.

232
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:21,900
Work with us, Bok.

233
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,567
I repeat.

234
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:27,167
We don't want to arrest you,

235
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:30,333
We want to arrest the head of
the syndicate.

236
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,833
Bok!

237
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:47,400
- Are you okay?
- I'm okay, Sir.

238
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:49,433
Give me your handcuffs.

239
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:57,733
I'm right, Garcia.

240
00:12:57,867 --> 00:13:00,467
You only solve cases
because of Tonyo.

241
00:13:04,133 --> 00:13:07,067
Bok, you take care of Bautista.

242
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:22,700
What? Is the live feedback?

243
00:13:22,867 --> 00:13:24,433
Not yet.

244
00:13:24,567 --> 00:13:25,733
This is crazy.

245
00:13:25,867 --> 00:13:27,333
Oh my God.

246
00:13:30,867 --> 00:13:34,367
<i> Samson, we now have Robles.</i>

247
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:35,333
Follow up on the ambulance.

248
00:13:35,467 --> 00:13:36,967
Copy, Ma'am.

249
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:40,067
Mayor, they say
they have Robles.

250
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,233
Noble, please save Chief.

251
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:01,700
Boss..

252
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:02,967
Mayor...

253
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,933
Mayor!

254
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:19,800
Bok, where did that come from?

255
00:14:24,867 --> 00:14:26,733
Conde!

256
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:28,367
Robles...

257
00:15:04,933 --> 00:15:05,500
Sorry, but you're only allowed
up to here.

258
00:15:05,633 --> 00:15:06,900
You're not allowed to enter.

259
00:15:07,033 --> 00:15:08,133
Sir, answer us.

260
00:15:08,267 --> 00:15:09,733
What's the update on
what's going on inside?

261
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:10,800
Later, you're not allowed
to enter.

262
00:15:10,933 --> 00:15:12,167
Let her in.

263
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:13,667
Mira.

264
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:16,200
Mayor, please update us
on what's happening.

265
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,300
Earlier, we just heard
a gunshot.

266
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:20,333
What happened?

267
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:21,567
Oh, there! She's back.

268
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:23,467
She's back.

269
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,800
<i> Yes, Mira, of course...</i>

270
00:15:25,933 --> 00:15:27,967
Currently, the hostages...

271
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:30,233
<i>Major Flores, Lieutenant Dizon,</i>

272
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:32,100
<i>and Staff Sergeant Bautista
are safe.</i>

273
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:34,800
The hostage taker,

274
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:37,000
Lieutenant Regan Robles,
also surrendered,

275
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:39,300
<i>but unfortunately, he was shot.</i>

276
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:40,833
There was a shooter coming
from the outside,

277
00:15:40,967 --> 00:15:42,867
and he died right away.

278
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,700
He's dead already?

279
00:15:44,833 --> 00:15:47,033
OMG!

280
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:49,867
Do you have any idea
who did this?

281
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,967
<i> Well, we are not sure of that.</i>

282
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:55,933
<i>I'm sure bad people
targeted him.</i>

283
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:58,300
<i>But I want to assure
the people of Calabari...</i>

284
00:15:58,433 --> 00:16:01,767
that the police are
investigating this.

285
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:03,267
Oh, it's Tonyo!

286
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:04,567
Tonyo is alive!

287
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:09,367
- Thank you.
- My baby boy is alive!

288
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,267
Excuse me.
Make way.

289
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:25,567
- Make way.
- Move aside.

290
00:16:25,700 --> 00:16:30,700
The body of the hostage taker,
Lieutenant Regan Robles,

291
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:32,067
is currently being taken out,
while the hostages

292
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:35,400
have been taken to the hospital.

293
00:16:35,533 --> 00:16:37,267
Lieutenant Conde...

294
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,067
I'm going to the hospital now.

295
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,900
You can come with me.

296
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,733
Excuse me.

297
00:17:03,767 --> 00:17:05,300
Mar, Abdul...

298
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:07,633
I need to go see my coworkers.

299
00:17:07,767 --> 00:17:09,267
You guys take care
of grandmother first, okay?

300
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,467
Stay behind, Abdul!
I'll go with you!

301
00:17:15,633 --> 00:17:16,633
That's terrible, Bok, isn't it?

302
00:17:16,767 --> 00:17:20,000
A headshot
and no follow-up shots.

303
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:22,867
Robles was definitely
the target.

304
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,600
I have a feeling...

305
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:26,900
the one who gave orders to
Robles...

306
00:17:27,033 --> 00:17:28,433
is also the one who killed him.

307
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:30,700
Because Robles surrendered.

308
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:34,100
He could expose that, right?

309
00:17:34,233 --> 00:17:36,433
- Bok.
- Oh, any news?

310
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:37,967
Bok, negative.

311
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:39,700
We didn't ID the shooter.

312
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:42,233
And no witnesses either.

313
00:17:42,367 --> 00:17:45,133
He did a clean job.

314
00:17:45,267 --> 00:17:46,600
Why are you so quiet?

315
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,433
What are you thinking?

316
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:52,867
Lieutenant Conde.

317
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,800
Garcia, Dizon.

318
00:17:54,933 --> 00:17:56,600
Mayor.

319
00:17:56,733 --> 00:17:59,633
Well, I'm glad everyone's okay.

320
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:00,933
It's sad what happened,

321
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:03,733
but you're still
doing a good job.

322
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:05,133
Thank you, Mayor.

323
00:18:05,267 --> 00:18:09,167
But if you're going
to commend us, no need.

324
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,200
We're just doing our job.

325
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:13,700
- We're fine.
- Okay, okay, okay, nevermind.

326
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:15,867
I was going to, but...

327
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:19,267
since you said it, no need.

328
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,367
But on a lighter note,

329
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:25,400
it's good that you've lost one
bad egg in your ranks.

330
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:27,367
I'm sorry, Mayor,

331
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:30,000
but Robles is also our
colleague,

332
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:35,767
and I don't think
he was born a bad egg.

333
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,700
Maybe he just made
the wrong decisions,

334
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,100
got caught up in the situation,

335
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:42,900
or maybe he was just blinded
by money.

336
00:18:43,033 --> 00:18:47,233
The real bad egg is his boss.

337
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:49,433
Imagine he just used Robles,

338
00:18:49,567 --> 00:18:51,500
and then when he got caught,

339
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:54,000
He was killed just like that,

340
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,667
as if Robles' life was worthless

341
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,833
and he didn't benefit
from the person.

342
00:18:57,967 --> 00:19:00,133
And the worst part is,
until now,

343
00:19:00,267 --> 00:19:02,333
that person is still free.

344
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:04,100
Oh, well, I'm sorry.

345
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:07,667
I didn't mean to speak
about his death in a bad way.

346
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:10,033
But you're right,
Lieutenant Conde.

347
00:19:10,167 --> 00:19:13,633
We must catch those
who killed him,

348
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:16,900
especially those
who had him killed.

349
00:19:17,033 --> 00:19:20,033
They are the real enemies
of Calabari.

350
00:19:20,167 --> 00:19:22,133
That's right, that's right,
Mayor.

351
00:19:22,267 --> 00:19:27,800
You know, whoever killed Robles
should die slowly.

352
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:30,333
Cut off his head
with a nail cutter.

353
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,200
Don't worry, Mayor.

354
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:34,500
I'm sure whoever it is,

355
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:37,233
his world is getting smaller
and smaller.

356
00:19:37,367 --> 00:19:39,833
And it won't take long before,

357
00:19:39,967 --> 00:19:41,900
we catch him too.

358
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:44,767
I'll expect that,
Lieutenant Conde.

359
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:48,167
Okay, I have to go.

360
00:19:48,300 --> 00:19:50,600
I have things to attend to.

361
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:52,033
Lieutenant.

362
00:19:52,167 --> 00:19:53,600
Okay.

363
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:04,933
Oh...

364
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:07,567
Captain, take your medicine.

365
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:08,467
I'll put it here, okay?

366
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,533
Hey, who are you?

367
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,933
What are you doing here in my
room?

368
00:20:13,067 --> 00:20:13,900
Captain!

369
00:20:14,033 --> 00:20:15,500
You know, you don't know
how to prank.

370
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:17,200
Go ahead, take your medicine.

371
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:18,467
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

372
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:21,267
You're a thief, aren't you?
You're a thief, aren't you?

373
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,267
Where's my grandchild?
Where's Bobby?

374
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,800
Where? Bobby!

375
00:20:24,933 --> 00:20:26,833
Thief! Get out of here! Get out!

376
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,200
Are you serious?

377
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:29,267
What's serious?

378
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,867
I'm serious! You're a thief!

379
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,500
- Captain! It's Abdul!
- Bobby! Bobby!

380
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:33,667
I'm Abdul!

381
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,467
I'm the only goddess of beauty,
remember?

382
00:20:36,633 --> 00:20:38,367
I always go with you
to the market, right?

383
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,633
Besides, I'm the one who's
always pretty in this house.

384
00:20:40,767 --> 00:20:42,633
You're the hairy thief!

385
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:44,433
Get out of here!

386
00:20:44,567 --> 00:20:46,633
No! Captain,
stop in the name of love!

387
00:20:46,767 --> 00:20:47,867
No, you're having an attack.

388
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,400
- Go ahead, drink this.
- What attack?

389
00:20:49,533 --> 00:20:52,267
You won't leave?
You're not leaving here?

390
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,700
- You're not leaving?
- Go ahead, drink this.

391
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:55,067
You're not leaving?

392
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,733
- Ouch! Captain!
- Bobby!

393
00:20:56,867 --> 00:20:58,900
- There's a thief here, Bobby!
- Ouch! Oh!

394
00:20:59,033 --> 00:21:00,733
- Bobby! Bobby!
- Ouch!

395
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:03,300
- I can't see anything! Ouch!
- Bobby!

396
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,833
Didn't you notice anything
about the mayor?

397
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:13,000
Did you notice it too?

398
00:21:13,133 --> 00:21:15,100
His eyes are so deeply set.

399
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:17,967
He looks like he has no more
nutrients in his body.

400
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:22,067
I don't know
why Cecilia liked him.

401
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,533
That's not it!

402
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:26,033
What do you mean, Bok?

403
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:28,033
I just noticed..

404
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:30,433
When Regan was shot,

405
00:21:30,567 --> 00:21:34,033
well, there was no sign of shock
or trauma on his face.

406
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:36,067
The person was right
next to him.

407
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:39,633
I'm a police officer,
and I was still shocked.

408
00:21:39,767 --> 00:21:42,200
So what are you pointing at?

409
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:44,200
No, Bok, I'm just wondering.

410
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,500
After Regan was shot,

411
00:21:48,633 --> 00:21:50,733
you saw it, he immediately
gave an interview to Mira.

412
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:52,833
Bok, of course, he's the mayor.

413
00:21:52,967 --> 00:21:54,567
He'll give an interview.

414
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,167
Any politician,

415
00:21:56,300 --> 00:21:58,900
if there's an opportunity for
someone to ask him a question,

416
00:21:59,033 --> 00:22:01,700
he'll try to be a good shot.

417
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:04,133
No, Bok, I feel differently.

418
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:06,667
I'm just wondering because...

419
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,967
his concern seems fake.

420
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:12,233
Tonyo!

421
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,933
That's why we get bashed
in the movies...

422
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:39,167
because of people like you.

423
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:40,433
The action is over,

424
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:41,933
and now you just show up.

425
00:22:42,067 --> 00:22:44,433
Eric! I thought something bad
had happened to you.

426
00:22:44,567 --> 00:22:46,300
The hostage taking was terrible.

427
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:47,167
I'm okay.

428
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:49,133
Morgana Lumibao!

429
00:22:51,267 --> 00:22:52,100
Who are you?

430
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:53,833
Donabelle Mae Custudio.

431
00:22:53,967 --> 00:22:54,767
Donabelle?

432
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:57,833
Your one and only ex
from high school!

433
00:22:57,967 --> 00:22:59,633
Enriquez, how are you?

434
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:00,500
Are you coming back?

435
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:02,500
I'm resigning, Chief.
